<HEADLINE>
<P>
TIMES CHESS COLUMNIST TO PLAY IN S.D. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jack Peters, chess columnist for The Times and an international master of the 
game, will be featured Sunday at the Bill Glass Memorial Action Tournament. 
</P>
<P>
The Balboa Chess Club is host of the daylong event that begins at 9 a.m. in its 
clubhouse, 6th Avenue and Ivy Street in Balboa Park. Cash prizes as high as 
$325 will be awarded to the best open and reserve players in the 
time-controlled games. The entry fee is $38 at the door for open players, or 
$33 for reserve players. 
</P>
<P>
Peters will also play a simultaneous exhibition at 7:30 p.m. Saturday at the 
Chess Club. Cost is $4 for spectators and $20 per board for players. For 
information, call 287-0089. 
</P>
