<P>
Former KCBS anchorwoman Terry Murphy will join the staff of a new syndicated 
news program, "Hard Copy," as a co-anchor. Also anchoring the program will be 
Alan Frio. "Hard Copy" is a half-hour news program produced by Paramount 
Television that debuts Sept. 18 on KNBC at 7:30 p.m. The show will also be seen 
in 129 other markets nationally. Most recently , Murphy was an anchor for the 6 
p.m. and 11 p.m. news broadcasts on KCBS. Frio was a news anchor at a 
Philadelphia station. CLAUDIA PUIG 
