<HEADLINE>
<P>
1 KILLED IN ACCIDENT NEAR FRAZIER PARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
One person died in a fiery three-vehicle accident Thursday night on the Golden 
State Freeway about 10 miles north of Frazier Park, according to the California 
Highway Patrol. 
</P>
<P>
The accident, which occurred about 8 p.m., involved a semitrailer truck loaded 
with rolled wire, a passenger car and a rental truck. 
</P>
<P>
When police arrived, the truck was engulfed in flames in the center divider. 
The driver was severely injured and taken by ambulance to Bakersfield, said CHP 
Sgt. Ron Lagrande. 
</P>
<P>
The passenger car contained a body that was too severely burned to identify, 
said Officer Andy Gutierrez. 
</P>
<P>
Lagrande said the semitrailer brakes appeared to have overheated as the truck 
descended the northbound slope of the Grapevine. Witnesses said the brakes were 
shooting flames before the crash. 
</P>
<P>
Traffic was halted in both directions for at least two hours as the CHP 
investigated and debris was cleared. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA081889-0051 </DOCNO>
