<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: BRAWL ERUPTS OVER WIDENING OF STREET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fistfights and shoving matches erupted outside a homeowners' meeting in Encino 
on Thursday evening as residents who disagree over whether Reseda Boulevard 
should be extended clashed outside an elementary school. 
</P>
<P>
The scuffles, involving about 10 people, occurred before a meeting organized by 
the Encino Property Owners Assn. and the Encino Hillside Traffic Safety 
Organization. The groups are asking that Reseda Boulevard be lengthened to 
Mulholland Drive to alleviate heavy traffic on Havenhurst Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
Members of a group called the Friends of Caballero Canyon confronted the Encino 
residents outside the Lanai Road Elementary School auditorium, and the shouting 
and shoving began. The Caballero Canyon group carried signs protesting the 
proposed Reseda Boulevard paving, saying it would bring additional development 
and threaten wildlife. 
</P>
<P>
City Councilman Marvin Braude was besieged by the crowd outside the school. 
Several shouted that they were being excluded from the meeting, attended by 
about 300 people. 
</P>
<P>
Police dispersed the protesters, who had been banging on the school doors. 
There were no arrests. 
</P>
</TEXT>
