Brian Lonon, five-time Army boxing champion, has been arrested in Killeen, 
Tex., and accused of cocaine possession. 
</P>
<P>
Police said they arrested Lonon at his home after finding cocaine valued at 
about $50,000. 
</P>
<P>
Officials of the U.S. boxing team said they were uncertain whether Lonon's 
arrest will keep him from competing for the U.S. team in the World 
Championships at Moscow next month. 
</P>
