<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: REAL ESTATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Compiled by Michael Flagg, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Marriott hotel chain said it will build another Courtyard by Marriott hotel 
in Laguna Hills. 
</P>
<P>
The $10-million, 137-room hotel is expected to open next spring. 
</P>
<P>
Marriott has already built two of the medium-priced Courtyard hotels in Orange 
County, in Buena Park and Santa Ana. A third, in Irvine near John Wayne 
Airport, will open in December. 
</P>
<P>
Room rates for the Laguna Hills hotel will run $74 on weekdays, $50 on 
weekends. Compiled by Michael Flagg, Times staff writer 
</P>
