<TEXT>
<P>
Money Supply Rises: The Federal Reserve Board reported that the nation's money 
supply, known as M1, rose in the week ended Aug. 7 to a seasonally adjusted 
$778.7 billion from $775.7 billion. The Fed said the measure known as M2 rose 
to a seasonally adjusted $3,132.4 billion from $3,127.5 billion the week 
before. M1 includes cash in circulation, deposits in checking accounts and 
non-bank travelers checks. M2 is M1 plus accounts such as savings deposits and 
money market mutual funds. 
</P>
