</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MANCHESTER, England 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Manchester United, one of the world's most famous soccer clubs, was sold today 
in a surprise deal worth more than $31 million, a record for a British club. 
</P>
<P>
A consortium led by Isle of Man-based businessman Michael Knighton paid United 
Chairman Martin Edwards $15.8 million for his controlling interest in the 
English First Division club. 
</P>
<P>
The buyers said up to $15.6 million would be spent on redeveloping the club's 
famous Old Trafford ground. 
</P>
<P>
Edwards, chairman for 9 1/2 years, will stay on as vice chairman and chief 
executive. 
</P>
</TEXT>
